Male genitalia (
Figs. 7 ‐ 9
). Sternite 9 produced into wide, shallowly bilobed subgenital plate. Tergite 10 central sclerite curved downwards at half length to fit neatly between arms of epiproct base. Medially on rounded hind margin of tergite 10 is a minute cone shaped posterior sclerite. Arms of epiproct curve down and posteriorly, then join and curve upwards and posteriorly, terminating in a downcurved sharp tip. Paraprocts large, about as long as cerci, broadly falcate, inner face from base to about half length forms a triangular membranous sheet. Membranous penis inside sternite 9, visible only in cleared specimens. The everted penis appears relatively dark, apparently through tissue pushed into it by body fluid pressure. It is a large pointed cone slightly curved up between the paraproct bases, lying below the epiproct hook and is partly divided longitudinally by a lateral fold ( Fig. 9 ). A tiny gonopore apparently at tip of slightly longer anterior part. A small triangular wing embracing base of paraproct observed only on the left side of body of the single specimen with everted penis.

Larva. (
Figs. 11 ‐ 17
). Short, stout, hairless and dusty brown. Surface matt because of numerous shallow pupillate punctures.
